    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere are quite some functions that show a message to the user, all with subtle differences:\n\n- `vim.notify`\n- `vim.api.nvim_echo`\n- `print`\n- `vim.print`\n\nAnd probably more that I'm forgetting. It's confusing which one is 'best' to use.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither recommend one or have one line that explains the difference between i.e. `vim.notify` and `nvim_echo`.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That's a bit premature since this is all very much in flux (especially with the ui2 rework).",
