        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "A goal of ui2 is that plugins should just be able to show \"normal\" messages (`:echo`, `nvim_echo`, `print`), and errors are always `error()` (or `assert()`). \n\n`vim.notify` was a workaround for the lack of control over message presentation, history, pager, and hooks. It will be very much deprecated when ui2 becomes default. Anything `vim.notify` \"feature\" which isn't addressed by \"normal\" messages should be fixed in... the message system.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-11T20:57:32Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/35654#issuecomment-4425130515",
            "id": 4425130515,
